<image 1> is not a regular graph because

A. not all edges are the same length
B. it is a complete graph
C. not all vertices have the same degree
D. it has a vertex of degree 3

To determine if the graph is not a regular graph, we need to check if all vertices have the same degree. A regular graph is a graph in which all vertices have the same degree.

In the given graph, we can see that vertices \(a\), \(b\), \(c\), and \(d\) have degree 3, while vertices \(e\), \(f\), and \(h\) have degree 2. Therefore, not all vertices have the same degree.

Therefore, the correct answer is:

C. not all vertices have the same degree
